1
00:00:00,667 --> 00:00:02,918
My name is Ali Zaki Suleiman al-Omari

2
00:00:04,167 --> 00:00:06,834
My education ended at primary school

3
00:00:10,083 --> 00:00:11,959
I’m married and I have children

4
00:00:12,959 --> 00:00:15,792
I’m 48 years old

5
00:00:16,834 --> 00:00:20,042
I work as a carpenter in decoration and design

6
00:00:22,834 --> 00:00:26,042
I was detained three times

7
00:00:27,584 --> 00:00:29,334
I was detained because of cigarettes

8
00:00:30,250 --> 00:00:32,042
And because of prayer, and because of the <i>izar</i> [long pants]

9
00:00:38,959 --> 00:00:42,500
Interviewer: In what year and month were you detained in this prison?

10
00:00:43,083 --> 00:00:48,167
And what was the charge that was brought against you?

11
00:00:48,292 --> 00:00:52,083
The first time was in 2015

12
00:00:53,542 --> 00:00:55,125
I was detained because of cigarettes

13
00:00:56,375 --> 00:00:59,584
When they started banning them gradually, then banned them completely

14
00:01:00,250 --> 00:01:03,167
They caught me smoking a cigarette, so they detained me

15
00:01:05,417 --> 00:01:07,334
I stayed six days because of cigarettes

16
00:01:09,042 --> 00:01:10,459
They caught me again

17
00:01:11,000 --> 00:01:13,500
That was the second time, because of the <i>izar</i> of my pants

18
00:01:14,751 --> 00:01:17,626
They whipped me and imprisoned me for four days

19
00:01:18,584 --> 00:01:21,918
The third time was for one day because of prayer

20
00:01:23,834 --> 00:01:27,042
He told me in the street, Go into the mosque. I said, I’ll go in

21
00:01:27,500 --> 00:01:30,292
But I didn’t, I turned from the other side, and he caught me

22
00:01:31,918 --> 00:01:33,250
They imprisoned me for just one day

23
00:01:35,918 --> 00:01:39,918
Interviewer: Do you remember the details of your arrival at this place?

24
00:01:40,918 --> 00:01:44,500
Yes, the first time this was their base

25
00:01:45,918 --> 00:01:49,000
When they caught me the first time this was their base

26
00:01:52,584 --> 00:01:54,000
Meaning the interrogation was inside

27
00:01:54,751 --> 00:01:58,876
They took me out of the car and brought me here on foot

28
00:01:59,751 --> 00:02:02,834
When we entered there was a reception desk where they wrote your name

29
00:02:03,375 --> 00:02:05,292
And the room inside was for interrogation

30
00:02:06,584 --> 00:02:09,751
When you go in, you see it there

31
00:02:10,125 --> 00:02:11,500
It was for interrogation

32
00:02:12,918 --> 00:02:15,250
When interrogation ended, they took you to prison

33
00:02:17,417 --> 00:02:20,834
The prison wasn’t in the same place, it was behind, over there

34
00:02:22,000 --> 00:02:23,667
Now it’s destroyed

35
00:02:23,834 --> 00:02:25,125
It used to be a church too

36
00:02:26,417 --> 00:02:29,459
In prison you were blindfolded

37
00:02:30,792 --> 00:02:35,834
They blindfolded you when they whipped you for example

38
00:02:35,834 --> 00:02:38,167
Or during interrogation, so you wouldn’t know who it was

39
00:02:41,709 --> 00:02:43,667
Interviewer: Did they beat you while bringing you here?

40
00:02:43,667 --> 00:02:45,834
No, they didn’t beat anyone outside

41
00:02:46,083 --> 00:02:47,918
But when you arrive in the prison, they beat you

42
00:02:48,375 --> 00:02:50,959
Interviewer: Did you know about this prison before you came here?

43
00:02:51,918 --> 00:02:56,250
No, I didn’t know. We only knew it was a Hisba base

44
00:02:57,626 --> 00:02:59,125
But we didn’t know what was inside

45
00:03:02,125 --> 00:03:04,959
Interviewer: What did you feel when you arrived at this place?

46
00:03:05,834 --> 00:03:08,918
I don’t know what to tell you. It was a feeling of fear

47
00:03:10,542 --> 00:03:12,125
Fear would be in your heart

48
00:03:12,125 --> 00:03:14,209
Because you don’t know if you’ll get out or not

49
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:19,083
You don’t know if they’ll beat you or kill you, you don’t know

50
00:03:20,250 --> 00:03:22,000
When you go in, you don’t know what your fate is

51
00:03:23,209 --> 00:03:25,876
Do you understand what I mean, you don’t know what your fate is
